# Internal HTML Naming (Security by Obscurity)

When creating or renaming **family/internal** HTML pages in this repo, follow the project standard so URLs are not guessable.

## Pattern

- **Format:** `name_descriptor_randomId.html`
  - `name`: person or domain (e.g. `donald`, `tacie`, `wrestling`, `excalibur`)
  - `descriptor`: short generic label (e.g. `track`, `supplements`, `training`, `venture`)
  - `randomId`: **5–6 mixed alphanumeric characters** (e.g. `3vN7q`, `2yR5j`, `2pX4v`). No semantic meaning.

## Do NOT

- Put the year in the filename (e.g. `track_2026.html`, `training_2025.html`).
- Use fully descriptive topic names that make the page obvious (e.g. `donald_track_season_schedule.html`).

## Do

- Keep **link text / card labels** human-readable (e.g. "Track 2026", "Donald Supplement Plan"). Only the filename is obscured.

## Examples

- ✅ `donald_track_3vN7q.html` — Track season page
- ✅ `tacie_training_2pX4v.html` — Training directives
- ❌ `donald_track_2026.html`
- ❌ `tacie_2025_training.html`

